That's what he does.

24:51.485 --> 24:55.150
He makes us all his body and guess what's in his body?

24:57.092 --> 24:58.354
His life blood.

24:58.914 --> 25:00.736
And let me tell you something.

25:00.756 --> 25:01.857
And this is so awesome.

25:02.278 --> 25:06.743
When Jesus dies, He gives you His life.

25:07.383 --> 25:08.344
He dies for you.

25:09.005 --> 25:15.312
If I have something and I give it to you as a gift, who's is it?

25:18.836 --> 25:19.416
Isn't it yours?

25:19.757 --> 25:20.638
If I've given it to you?

25:21.298 --> 25:22.099
It's yours, right?

25:22.500 --> 25:24.842
So Jesus says, I'm giving you my body.

25:24.882 --> 25:25.463
Who's is it?

25:27.505 --> 25:28.306
It's yours.

25:28.866 --> 25:31.049
This is my body broken for you.

25:31.129 --> 25:34.032
He gives it to the disciples and said, this is for you.

25:34.052 --> 25:36.255
This is now your body.

25:36.295 --> 25:41.201
And he says afterward, now that you got the body, here's my blood.

25:41.401 --> 25:42.363
I give it to you.

25:43.624 --> 25:44.185
Who is it?

25:45.626 --> 25:46.347
It's ours.

25:47.309 --> 25:55.779
We have his body and his blood because he gave it to us, not because we're apart with him, but he gave it to us.

25:57.060 --> 25:58.322
We own it.

25:59.298 --> 26:02.201
That's incredible, even think that.

26:02.541 --> 26:09.268
But it changes the way we perceive ourselves and the way we see the world and other people in the faith, doesn't it?

26:12.271 --> 26:18.037
We are remolded into something brand new and that required us to have a new spiritual body.

26:20.900 --> 26:26.706
Chameleon then is the outward sign of the actuality

26:26.914 --> 26:32.940
of God's recreating work in us when Christ gives us his body and his blood.

26:37.224 --> 26:40.868
You understand when he dies, it's a gift to you.

26:42.409 --> 26:44.691
And so you own his death and resurrection.

26:45.252 --> 26:47.554
You own it because he gave it to you.

26:49.036 --> 26:55.442
But he gave it to you because you trusted him and would receive it in faith.

26:57.794 --> 27:04.945
During communion, we agree with what Jesus said, and we remember what He did and why.

27:05.606 --> 27:14.479
One of the devotional students, St. Andrews this week said, the mystery of communion is Christ has died, Christ has risen, and Christ will come again.

27:14.519 --> 27:15.521
That's what we said.

27:16.382 --> 27:27.058
In communion, what Jesus says in Corinthians is, this is my body, take any, do this,

27:28.002 --> 27:29.303
Remembering what I did for you.

27:30.324 --> 27:31.646
Remembering what I gave you.

27:32.687 --> 27:35.310
And when we take the cup, he says, this is my blood.

27:35.710 --> 27:37.612
And it's poured out for you for your forgiveness.

27:37.852 --> 27:38.753
It's a new covenant.

27:38.933 --> 27:41.756
It's not the old thing you've been thinking about living your whole life.

27:41.776 --> 27:44.099
This is something you've never experienced before.

27:44.139 --> 27:45.880
Remember what I gave you.

27:47.682 --> 27:52.687
And so every time we take communion, we remember again that we are not who we were.

27:53.368 --> 27:55.250
We are who Christ says we are.

28:01.858 --> 28:30.418
First Corinthians chapter 11 where Paul tells the institution he closes it with this in verse 26 Where as often as you eat this bread and drink this cup you proclaim the Lord's death till he comes But you proclaim that it was given for you and to you He gives himself to you in his death You say well, how does that make sense that?

28:31.426 --> 28:32.367
Then he did that.

28:32.868 --> 28:40.557
Listen, when he told the disciples with this unleavened bread before he died, this is my body.

28:41.999 --> 28:42.840
Was he dead yet?

28:42.860 --> 28:43.942
No.

28:44.462 --> 28:47.045
And he said, this is my blood and a cup poured out for you.

28:47.326 --> 28:48.167
Was he dead yet?

28:48.848 --> 28:50.570
No, it was symbolic.

28:51.791 --> 28:52.813
It was an actuality.

28:52.833 --> 28:54.134
It was about to happen.

28:54.755 --> 29:00.402
And he said, so remember what I've done for you in communion is symbolic for what actually occurred.

29:04.098 --> 29:16.495
So when we partake, it's just like they did because it's not actually Jesus' flesh and blood, it's the spiritual reality of what He does for us and did for us.

29:16.515 --> 29:22.703
And that's why we come to the communion table, thankful and humble and grateful because it was all about Him.

29:25.446 --> 29:27.589
We are new creations in Christ.

29:27.649 --> 29:34.098
We have His lifeblood in us made possible because of His death and resurrection.

29:35.490 --> 29:36.451
You are brand new.

29:37.813 --> 29:38.794
You are brand new.

29:40.416 --> 29:48.266
Now you have to learn how to renew your mind to understand your spiritual place and the reality of who you are in Jesus Christ.

29:48.867 --> 29:50.028
And that takes time to learn.

29:50.068 --> 29:52.351
To be deciphered.

29:52.812 --> 30:01.443
The temptation is to believe that this didn't really happen to us as we're just the same as we've always been.

30:01.503 --> 30:03.986
That's the temptation.

30:04.130 --> 30:06.333
And that's why we need communion to remind us.

30:07.154 --> 30:13.344
This is why Jesus said, as often as you do this, remember what I've done for you because you're going to forget.

30:13.364 --> 30:18.231
And you're going to thank you still who you were before I came into your life.

30:20.214 --> 30:21.736
And we need that reminder, don't we?

30:24.300 --> 30:25.542
So what did I learn that day?

30:25.562 --> 30:30.409
I had to have a new body to have the new blood.

30:33.113 --> 30:34.034
So you can't put

30:34.754 --> 30:36.697
new wine and old wine skins.

30:37.558 --> 30:45.248
You need a new wine skin, a new body, the house, the new wine, which is the blood and life of Christ.

30:45.929 --> 30:47.210
And so he gives you both.

30:48.132 --> 30:49.834
That's what that parable is saying.

30:50.515 --> 30:52.217
And he doesn't patchwork you up.

30:52.477 --> 30:53.539
He makes it new.

30:56.042 --> 30:59.927
That is such a blessing in what we celebrate in Holy Communion.

31:01.009 --> 31:01.970
Would you pray with me?

31:03.074 --> 31:10.025
Heavenly Father, thank You for giving us to life in Christ and for forgiving us as You did so.

31:10.926 --> 31:14.271
Lord, we thank You that You knew us, that You love us, that You care for us.

31:15.092 --> 31:20.160
And I ask You to establish us now as we prepare for Holy Communion in the mystery of the faith.

31:20.220 --> 31:29.554
The Christ died, Christ has risen, Christ's will come again, and we are His body and blood to the world around us, filled with who He is.

31:30.786 --> 31:33.929
No matter what we might think or say, the world doesn't understand.

31:33.989 --> 31:38.314
And we're learning to acknowledge what you've done innocent to us.

31:38.754 --> 31:39.074
Amen.

31:44.180 --> 31:50.686
As we prepare for Holy Communion this morning, I ask you to consider that Christ has made you bread now.

31:51.847 --> 31:58.514
And when you've taken, received the bread in a cup, that as you receive that, it's reminding you

31:58.722 --> 32:01.447
what he did in you to you spiritually.

32:02.028 --> 32:04.933
This is an outward sign of an actuality.

32:05.534 --> 32:08.640
That's why we received it humbly because only he could do that.

32:09.141 --> 32:13.949
We could not do anything but make a patchwork mess of our lives.

32:14.450 --> 32:15.592
So he made us brand new.

32:15.752 --> 32:21.202
Thankfully that work is a completed work on the cross.

